title: A Quiet Election Day In Iraq, With Some Signs For Concern
teaser: For the first time since U.S. troops withdrew in 2011, Iraqis went to the polls to vote on their leaders. As Reuters reporter Ned Parker says, the day's events paint a grim future for Iraq's future.
